message.content:
A pitcher is a container typically used for pouring beverages, such as water, juice or beer. 
It is usually cylindrical in shape and has a spout for easy pouring. 
Pitchers can vary in size, depending on their intended use, but are usually smaller than a jug.
They may be made of various materials such as glass, ceramic, or metal. 
Some pitchers may have decorative designs on them, while others may be plain. 
Pitchers are commonly found in households, restaurants, and bars. 
They are also used in sports such as baseball and cricket to throw the ball.
